<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-12-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="577" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Bliss</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-12-28"><hi rend="italic">December 28,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President returned last night; approves your December 19. Argentine
                            minister for foreign affairs is instructing Argentine minister at Lima
                            to act with representatives of the United States and Brazil in
                            accordance with your December 22, to Petropolis, and at the same time to
                            telegraph minister for foreign affairs of Ecuador in a like sense.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>